com.innowhere.jnieasy.core.method
Interface NativeFieldMethodReflection

All Superinterfaces:
CanBeNativeCapable, NativeBehavior, NativeBehaviorReflection, NativeCallback, NativeCapable, NativeFieldCallback, NativeFieldContainer, NativeFieldMethod, NativeMemberReflection, NativeObjectFieldContainer, NativeSingleFieldContainer
All Known Subinterfaces:
NativeInstanceFieldMethodReflection, NativeStaticFieldMethodReflection
public interface NativeFieldMethodReflection
extends NativeBehaviorReflection, NativeFieldCallback

The NativeFieldMethodReflection is the interface implemented by native capable classes that make accessible Java fields from native seen as methods. Java fields are accessed using Java reflection.

Author:
Jose M. Arranz Santamaria
See Also:
